          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Small Business Surcharge Relief Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the National Flood Insurance Act of 1968 to partially exempt small businesses and nonprofit organizations from the Homeowner Flood Insurance Affordability Act (HFIAA) surcharge. The bill limits application of the HFIAA surcharge to two buildings on the same property, exempting additional buildings. The business or organization must certify that the savings will be used for flood mitigation on the property.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-11-07T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
